    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - PRIMING FUEL INJECTION
        SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PRIMING FUEL INJECTION SYSTEM</title>
        <para>After replacing fuel injection pump or replacing fuel supply lines, prime fuel system using these
            procedures:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the bleed screw at the pump fuel inlet.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen hand priming pump handle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Operate priming pump until pump action provides solid fuel at bleed screw. Close screw.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position injection pump shutoff lever in run position with electric shutoff or mechanical
                cable.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Crank engine for fifteen seconds.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten priming pump handle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start engine and operate until engine runs smoothly.</para>
            <figure id="ef4151158" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11658" filename="../figcg1/CG11658.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.58. Install a New Fuel Filter.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
